4:["$","article",null,{"className":"pt-36 pb-32 px-6","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-8","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"pill-tag text-xs font-semibold px-3 py-1 rounded-full","children":"Etsy SEO"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs","style":{"color":"#404060"},"children":"April 2025 · 8 min read"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"font-black leading-tight mb-6","style":{"fontSize":"clamp(30px, 4.5vw, 46px)","lineHeight":1.15},"children":"Why Your Etsy Listings Get No Views (And How to Fix It)"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg mb-12 leading-relaxed","style":{"color":"#8080a0"},"children":"You spent hours photographing your products, writing a description, setting up your shop — and you're getting single-digit weekly views. Maybe zero. It feels personal. It isn't. It's almost always fixable, and the fix is almost never what you think it is."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"First: Understand How Etsy Search Actually Works"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Etsy is a search engine with a marketplace attached. Every time a buyer opens the app or site and types a query, Etsy's algorithm runs through millions of listings and decides which ones to surface — and in what order."}],["$","p",null,{"children":["The algorithm weighs several factors: ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"relevancy"}]," (do your title, tags, and attributes match what the buyer typed?), ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"listing quality score"}]," (do buyers click and buy when they see this listing?), ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"recency"}]," (has this listing been renewed or updated recently?), and ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"shop quality"}]," (reviews, completion rate, shipping performance)."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Most sellers with zero views have a relevancy problem, not a quality problem. Your listing is beautiful. Etsy just doesn't know who to show it to."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"reason-block","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"reason-label","children":"Problem 1"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"fix-label","children":"Fixable"}]]}],["$","h3",null,{"style":{"marginTop":0},"children":"Your Title Isn't Matching Real Search Queries"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"This is the most common cause of zero views. If your title is \"Blue Ceramic Mug — Handmade Pottery,\" Etsy has almost no idea what search queries to rank you for. \"Handmade\" appears in 3 million listings. \"Ceramic mug\" is searched by people who are browsing, not buying."}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"The fix:"}]," Research what buyers actually type. Use Etsy's autocomplete — type \"ceramic mug\" and look at every dropdown suggestion. Those are real searches happening right now. You might find \"ceramic mug for plant lover\" (247,000 searches/month) or \"coffee mug gift for teacher\" (89,000 searches). Pick the one that fits your product and lead your title with it."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Your full title should be 120–140 characters and read like a natural sentence, not a keyword list. \"Coffee Mug Gift for Teacher — Handmade Blue Ceramic, Funny Appreciation Gift, End of Year Teacher Gift\" is better than \"Ceramic Mug Blue Handmade Pottery Coffee Tea Gift.\""}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"reason-block","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"reason-label","children":"Problem 2"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"fix-label","children":"Fixable"}]]}],["$","h3",null,{"style":{"marginTop":0},"children":"Your Tags Are All Single Words"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Single-word tags are a waste. \"Mug\" as a tag means you're competing with every mug seller on the platform for a keyword that converts at almost zero percent. Buyers who search just \"mug\" are window-shopping, not buying."}],"$L9","$La"]}],"$Lb","$Lc","$Ld","$Le","$Lf","$L10","$L11","$L12"]}],"$L13"]}]}]
